of art market navel-gazing. Tonight, we=E2=80=99re going to talk about the =
record-setting $32 million sale of one of the pairs of ruby slippers that J=
udy Garland wore as Dorothy in The Wizard of Oz. In a heated auction that r=
an from a $1.5 million opening bid to a $28 million final hammer price, the=
 ne plus ultra of movie memorabilia achieved a price five or six times the =
previous record for movie or popular culture objects. The sale is a milesto=
ne in the expanding world of cultural property. But that=E2=80=99s only the=
