ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">I=E2=80=99m <b>Marion</b> <=
b>Maneker</b>, and this is Wall Power, your twice-weekly dose of art market=
 navel-gazing. <br/><br/>Tonight, we=E2=80=99re going to talk about the rec=
ord-setting $32 million sale of one of the pairs of ruby slippers that <b>J=
udy Garland</b> wore as Dorothy in <i>The Wizard of Oz</i>. In a heated auc=
tion that ran from a $1.5 million opening bid to a <i>$28 million </i>final=
 hammer price, the <i>ne plus ultra</i> of movie memorabilia achieved a pri=
ce <i>five or six times</i> the previous record for movie or popular cultur=
e objects. The sale is a milestone in the expanding world of cultural prope=
rty. But that=E2=80=99s only the beginning of the story. More on that below=
=2E<br/><br/><i>But first=E2=80=A6</i><br/=
><br/><i>Wall Power is expanding!</=
i>: Today=E2=80=99s newsletter is heavy on design and memorabilia. Part of =
the reason is the news cycle, but it=E2=80=99s also
because this provides a good opportunity to announce that we=E2=80=99re exp=
anding Wall Power to four days a week beginning in January. The newsletter =
will continue to publish every Sunday and Tuesday, but we=E2=80=99re adding=
 two more sends: one on Friday, for all subscribers, and another on Wednesd=
ay, available to Inner Circle members only. (<u><a href=3D"https://email.pu=
ck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUelRQOWhtTDgxc0toMEp=
VXzZnMD0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvam9pbi8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVdhbG=
