ee898be09ad2" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold"=
 class=3D"sdf">Click here</a></u> to upgrade your subscription.)<br/><br/>W=
ith the expanded space comes expanded coverage. We=E2=80=99ll be reporting =
on even more of the art world=E2=80=94more coverage of museums and the deci=
sion-makers at those institutions, as well as the broader world of cultural=
 property, such as design, luxury items, and memorabilia. (When footwear, e=
ven the <i>most </i>famous footwear, sells for $32 million, it=E2=80=99s ti=
me to look beyond fine art.) <br/><br/>I=E2=80=99ve often suggested in the =
past
that there=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cmissing money=E2=80=9D in the art market, a s=
imple observation that auction totals have not kept up with the overall ris=
e in wealth. Rich people tend to spend a consistent portion of their money =
on things like art. So maybe they=E2=80=99re buying other cultural property=
 that is valued and sold like art? That=E2=80=99s a supposition I=E2=80=99d=
 like to explore further.<br/> <br/>To help us with all that, I=E2=80=99m t=
hrilled to announce that <b>Julie Brener Davich</b> is joining Wall Power. =
Julie spent more than two decades working in the art and design industries,=
 including at Christie=E2=80=99s and Sotheby=E2=80=99s, but also as a journ=
alist at <i>Town &amp; Country, Art &amp; Auction</i>, and <i>ARTnews. </i>=
As you=E2=80=99ll see for yourself, she understands how the specialists, ma=
rketers, and dealmakers actually value cultural property, and how art is so=
ld. And she fits perfectly into Puck, which values true domain expertise. A=
s you know, my partner <b>Bill Cohan </b>was a banker before he covered fin=
ance
exquisitely; <b>Matt Belloni </b>was an entertainment lawyer before he beca=
me the industry=E2=80=99s most exalted journalist; <b>Dylan Byers </b>was o=
n CNN, once upon a time, before he became its informal H.R. department. I=
=E2=80=99m <i>excited</i> to welcome Julie to Wall Power, and I hope you ar=
e too. <br/></p>
