x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">There=E2=80=99s ano=
ther piece to the slippers=E2=80=99 allure, of course: They were stolen alm=
ost 20 years ago. A similar theft is also at the heart of the global celebr=
ity of the <i>Mona Lisa</i>. Most people who crowd into the Louvre museum t=
o view that painting don=E2=80=99t know that <i>La Joconde</i>, as the Fren=
ch call it, spent centuries in relative obscurity before it was stolen by a=
n Italian patriot in 1911, in the aftermath of which a French newspaper war=
 transformed the painting into one of the most famous objects in the world.=
  <br/><br/>It took two years to recover the <i>Mona Lisa</i> and return it=
 to France. Recovering Dorothy=E2=80=99s ruby slippers took a bit longer. T=
he shoes, along with the rest of MGM=E2=80=99s costume archive, some 350,00=
0 items, had been languishing in storage when, after the studio was sold to=
 <b>Kirk Kerkorian</b> in 1969, costume
designer <b>Kent</b> <b>Warner</b> was given the task of searching the trov=
e for items that could be sold at auction. Warner found several pairs of th=
e ruby slippers in the mountain of dross, one of which was sold in the subs=
equent auction for $15,000. (That pair eventually ended up in the Smithsoni=
an, where the foot traffic in front of the vitrine regularly makes the carp=
et threadbare.) Warner quietly sold another pair he=E2=80=99d found to a co=
llector named <b>Michael Shaw</b>, who toured them for years until, while s=
pending a summer on display at the Judy Garland Museum in her birthplace, G=
rand Rapids, Minnesota, the slippers were stolen. <br/><br/>For 13 years, t=
he mystery of who had stolen the ruby slippers and why animated the world o=
f pop culture memorabilia and fed into the broader fascination with Garland=
=E2=80=99s tragic life. There=E2=80=99s even a <u><a href=3D"https://email.=
puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUelRQOWhtTDgxc0toM=
EpVXzZnMD0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9vcGVuLnNwb3RpZnkuY29tL3Nob3cvME0wa2RxeU16=
N3NmQ1hwMnc0ZHZLWT9zaT00MDQ4MjM5MjY1ZjI0NWRmXHUwMDI2dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVdhbGw=
rUG93ZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMiUyRjE1JTJGMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD=
